From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: robert-brunson-fragile <siinspam@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 14:20:04 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 21/23] refactor(api)!: remove /v1/runs/{run_id}/events;
 persist run events durably
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The per-run SSE endpoint was single-consumer (the queue was popped on
first attach and the stream 404'd on reconnect) and non-durable — the
odd one out after /api/sessions/{id}/subscribe became the durable,
multi-consumer, resumable event surface.

- POST /v1/runs now registers the run in ResponseStore
  (create_session_run) and every event that used to feed the private
  asyncio.Queue — message.delta, tool.*, reasoning.available,
  approval.request/responded, run.started/completed/failed/cancelled —
  is persisted via a new _emit_run_event helper
  (put_session_run_event + subscriber notify). Any number of clients
  observe and replay them through /subscribe; the 202 response now
  includes session_id so clients know what to subscribe to.
- Approval flow keeps a polling-only path: approval.request is stashed
  as pending_approval in the run status (GET /v1/runs/{id} shows
  status=waiting_for_approval plus the redacted request) and cleared on
  response. _set_run_status now removes fields passed as None.
- run.failed / run.cancelled events map to failed / interrupted run
  statuses in ResponseStore.
- _run_streams/_run_streams_created replaced by _run_created_at;
  the concurrency cap counts _active_run_tasks; the orphan sweep only
  reaps runs whose task is gone or done (previously it could drop a
  long run's stop/approval bookkeeping mid-flight at the 300s TTL).
- Capabilities: run_events_sse=false, run_events endpoint entry
  removed. Website docs (en + zh-Hans) point at /subscribe.

Tests: run lifecycle events asserted against the durable store, stop
reaches a terminal durable state, approval flow verified via status
polling + durable replay, removed endpoint 404s.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

